<clause id="sec2-1" obligation="normative"><title>2.1.</title><p id="_9c821cf6-01c1-4263-8ba0-2f81b93d043e">The CCDM 1982 <eref type="inline" bibitemid="docs-metre" citeas="[1]">[1]</eref>, <eref type="inline" bibitemid="bipm-metre" citeas="[2]">[2]</eref> gives</p>
<p align="left" id="_8343cfc5-4408-4632-8779-838acbbb0a38"><stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msub><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">K</mi><mi>r</mi></mrow></mrow></msub><mo>/</mo><msub><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>i</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>1.044&#8239;919&#8239;242&#8239;05</mn></math></stem><br/>
<stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msub><mrow><mi>u</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>c</mi></mrow></msub><mo>/</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1.3</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mrow><mi>&#8722;</mi><mn>9</mn></mrow></mrow></msup></math></stem>,<br/>
using the recommended operation conditions <eref type="inline" bibitemid="bipmx2" citeas="[3]">[3]</eref>.</p>
<p id="_1f68321a-3ae0-4ca6-b809-a2ad89f41b21">Using the recommended value of the absorbing molecule <sup>127</sup>I<sub>2</sub>, <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msub><mrow><mtext>a</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>16</mn></mrow></msub></math></stem> or f component, R(127) 11-5 transition (see iodine at <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>&#955;</mi></mstyle><mo>&#8776;</mo><mn>633</mn><mo rspace="thickmathspace">&#8290;</mo><mrow xref="U_nm"><mi mathvariant="normal">nm</mi></mrow>








</math></stem> and frequency differences listed in corresponding Table 1) one obtains</p>
<p align="left" id="_4518f39b-456f-4fdd-8efc-89e3a8431318"><stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msub><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>i</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>473&#8239;612&#8239;214&#8239;712</mn><mo rspace="thickmathspace">&#8290;</mo><mrow xref="U_kHz"><mi mathvariant="normal">kHz</mi></mrow>








</math></stem><br/>
<stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msub><mrow><mi>u</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>c</mi></mrow></msub><mo>/</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2.2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mrow><mi>&#8722;</mi><mn>11</mn></mrow></mrow></msup></math></stem>,</p>
<p align="left" id="_fd75aa78-20ae-4bc5-95c8-e501e909942f">which leads to</p>
<p align="left" id="_c941ea4f-77fb-42dd-aac0-47135b9c7a0e"><stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msub><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">K</mi><mi>r</mi></mrow></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>494&#8239;886&#8239;516&#8239;422</mn><mo rspace="thickmathspace">&#8290;</mo><mrow xref="U_kHz"><mi mathvariant="normal">kHz</mi></mrow>








</math></stem><br/>
<stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msub><mrow><mi>u</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>c</mi></mrow></msub><mo>/</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1.3</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mrow><mi>&#8722;</mi><mn>9</mn></mrow></mrow></msup></math></stem>.</p></clause></clause>
